  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "There are countless iconic and memorable lines in English songs across various genres. Here are a few of the most celebrated and timeless lyrics:\n\n1. **The Beatles - \"Let It Be\"**  \n   *\"When I find myself in times of trouble, Mother Mary comes to me, speaking words of wisdom, let it be.\"*\n\n2. **Queen - \"Bohemian Rhapsody\"**  \n   *\"Is this the real life? Is this just fantasy? Caught in a landslide, no escape from reality.\"*\n\n3. **Bob Dylan - \"Like a Rolling Stone\"**  \n   *\"How does it feel, to be on your own, with no direction home, like a complete unknown, like a rolling stone?\"*\n\n4. **Leonard Cohen - \"Hallelujah\"**  \n   *\"It\u2019s not a cry that you hear at night, it\u2019s not somebody who\u2019s seen the light, it\u2019s a cold and it\u2019s a broken Hallelujah.\"*\n\n5. **John Lennon - \"Imagine\"**  \n   *\"Imagine all the people living life in peace.\"*\n\n6. **Whitney Houston - \"I Will Always Love You\"**  \n   *\"And I will always love you.\"*\n\n7. **Frank Sinatra - \"My Way\"**  \n   *\"I did it my way.\"*\n\n8. **Nirvana - \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\"**  \n   *\"Here we are now, entertain us.\"*\n\n9. **Adele - \"Someone Like You\"**  \n   *\"Never mind, I\u2019ll find someone like you.\"*\n\n10. **Simon & Garfunkel - \"The Sound of Silence\"**  \n    *\"Hello darkness, my old friend, I\u2019ve come to talk with you again.\"*\n\n11. **Eminem - \"Lose Yourself\"**  \n    *\"You only get one shot, do not miss your chance to blow, this opportunity comes once in a lifetime.\"*\n\n12. **Elton John - \"Your Song\"**  \n    *\"How wonderful life is while you\u2019re in the world.\"*\n\n13. **Lynyrd Skynyrd - \"Free Bird\"**  \n    *\"If I leave here tomorrow, would you still remember me?\"*\n\n14. **The Rolling Stones - \"(I Can't Get No) Satisfaction\"**  \n    *\"I can\u2019t get no satisfaction.\"*\n\n15. **Alicia Keys - \"Fallin\u2019\"**  \n    *\"I keep on fallin\u2019 in and out of love with you.\"*\n\nThese lines have resonated with millions of people around the world, often because of their emotional depth, poetic beauty, or universal themes. They continue to inspire and connect listeners across generations.",
